OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1775523444
OL,3,CTwo-child benefit cap ends and state
OL,4,Cpensions rise starting today
OL,6,FThe change to the policy was announced
OL,7,Fby Chancellor Rachel Reeves during the
OL,8,Fbudget last year, following months of
OL,9,Fpressure from Labour backbenchers.
OL,11,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,12,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,13,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,14,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,16,FElsewhere, state pensions will rise
OL,17,F4.8% rise in line with average wages,
OL,18,Fwhich will give millions of pensioners
OL,19,Fan additional #575 this year, the
OL,20,Fgovernment said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
