CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1775523444
OL,3,CTwo-child benefit cap ends and state
OL,4,Cpensions rise starting today
OL,6,FHousing benefit and personal
OL,7,Findependence payments are also being
OL,8,Fuprated from today, and fathers will
OL,9,Fno longer need six months of service
OL,10,Fbefore they're allowed to take
OL,11,Fpaternity leave.
OL,13,F"No matter the global uncertainty, my
OL,14,Fgovernment will always be on the side
OL,15,Fof the British people in bearing down
OL,16,Fon the cost of living," Prime Minister
OL,17,FKeir Starmer said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1775523444
OL,3,CTwo-child benefit cap ends and state
OL,4,Cpensions rise starting today
OL,6,F"I will never lose sight of how
OL,7,Frestless people are for change, and I
OL,8,Fam proud that today we are lifting
OL,9,Fnearly half a million children out of
OL,10,Fpoverty, boosting support for
OL,11,Fpensioners, and delivering the biggest
OL,12,Fupgrade to workers' rights in a
OL,13,Fgeneration."
OL,15,FStarmer also said he understood the
OL,16,Fconcern over the ongoing economic
OL,17,Fimpact of the US-Israeli war in Iran
OL,18,Fon the UK and other countries.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@LO]
